\f1\b \cf0 \strokec2 2. Case Study: N3 One Glass
\f0\b0  
\f1\b Accenture \'b7 Enterprise UX \'b7 AI-Assisted Design
\f0\b0 \

\f2\i As a senior UX/UI designer at Accenture, I was responsible for translating wireframes into a polished, production-ready interface \'97 balancing visual quality, usability, and seamless AI integration.
\f0\i0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \strokec2 The Challenge
\f0\b0  
\f1\b Redesigning the tool agents depend on every call
\f0\b0 \
Call center agents were working with an outdated tool that slowed preparation and limited their ability to connect meaningfully with customers before each interaction. The objective was to redesign this tool with AI-driven widgets that would surface relevant customer information upfront \'97 reducing friction and improving call efficiency.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \strokec2 Design
\f0\b0  
\f1\b From wireframes to a production-ready interface
\f0\b0 \
My role was to transform existing wireframes into a visually appealing, easy-to-use interface without losing fidelity to the original structure. This meant simplifying the UI for agents managing high call volumes, while integrating AI widgets in a way that felt natural and unobtrusive \'97 supportive, not distracting.\
Every design decision was made with the agent's workflow in mind: less time hunting for information, more time focused on the customer.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

