\f1\b \cf0 3. Case Study: Procurement Scrum Board
\f0\b0  
\f1\b Accenture \'b7 Enterprise UX \'b7 Internal Tooling
\f0\b0 \

\f2\i As a UX/UI designer, I was involved end-to-end \'97 from stakeholder calls with managers to final interface design \'97 ensuring the product was both efficient and easy to adopt.
\f0\i0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \strokec2 The Challenge
\f0\b0  
\f1\b Replacing a spreadsheet without losing what worked about it
\f0\b0 \
Procurement managers were running their scrum calls from Excel sheets \'97 functional, but fragile. Information lived outside the main tool, updates were manual, and collaboration was limited. The challenge was to design a native scrum board within the procurement platform that replicated the flexibility of a spreadsheet, while adding the capabilities a digital tool should offer: comments, custom filters, and table configuration.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \strokec2 Design
\f0\b0  
\f1\b Built around how managers actually work
\f0\b0 \
I participated directly in calls with managers to evaluate usability and understand their real workflow. This informed every design decision \'97 from how the table was structured to how filtering and customization were surfaced without adding complexity.\
The goal was a familiar feel with a meaningful upgrade: the comfort of a spreadsheet, the power of a connected tool.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

