\f1\b \cf0 \strokec2 4. Case Study: Talent Acquisition \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf0 \strokec2 End-to-end hiring platform serving candidates, managers, talent services, and operations.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 \strokec2 As part of a collaborative design team, I contributed to the end-to-end design of a multi-role hiring platform under tight delivery timelines.
\f0\i0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \strokec2 The Challenge
\f0\b0  
\f1\b Hiring at scale, without the chaos
\f0\b0 \
A fast-growing company in a highly competitive market needed a structured tool to manage its hiring process. The existing approach couldn't keep up with the volume or complexity of recruiting across multiple roles and stakeholders. The challenge was to design a unified platform that served four distinct users \'97 candidates, managers, talent services, and operations leaders \'97 each with different needs and levels of access.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 \strokec2 Design
\f0\b0  
\f1\b One platform, four perspectives
\f0\b0 \
The design required a deep understanding of each user's role in the hiring process. Interfaces were tailored to each profile: candidates needed clarity and guidance, managers needed pipeline visibility, talent services needed operational control, and operations leaders needed high-level oversight.\
Working as part of a design team, I contributed across multiple interfaces while maintaining consistency and meeting demanding delivery timelines.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
